Step 1 - 2

data <- read.csv('GermanCredit.csv')

model <- lm(Amount~.-X-Class,data=data)
#step(model)

model <- lm(formula = Amount ~ Duration + InstallmentRatePercentage + 
    Telephone + CheckingAccountStatus.0.to.200 + CheckingAccountStatus.gt.200 + 
    CreditHistory.NoCredit.AllPaid + Purpose.NewCar + Purpose.UsedCar + 
    Purpose.Furniture.Equipment + Purpose.Radio.Television + 
    Purpose.DomesticAppliance + Purpose.Repairs + Purpose.Education + 
    Purpose.Retraining + Purpose.Business + SavingsAccountBonds.lt.100 + 
    SavingsAccountBonds.100.to.500 + SavingsAccountBonds.500.to.1000 + 
    EmploymentDuration.gt.7 + Personal.Male.Single + OtherDebtorsGuarantors.CoApplicant + 
    Property.RealEstate + Property.Insurance + Property.CarOther + 
    Job.UnemployedUnskilled + Job.UnskilledResident + Job.SkilledEmployee, 
    data = data)

Step 3

coef <- c()
rsq <- c()
rsqtest <- c()
# loop for 1000 times
for (i in seq(1:1000)){
    picked <- sample(1000,size = 632)
    train_data <- data[picked,]
    test_data <- data[-picked,]
    
    model1 <- lm(formula = Amount ~ Duration + InstallmentRatePercentage + 
    Telephone + CheckingAccountStatus.0.to.200 + CheckingAccountStatus.gt.200 + 
    CreditHistory.NoCredit.AllPaid + Purpose.NewCar + Purpose.UsedCar + 
    Purpose.Furniture.Equipment + Purpose.Radio.Television + 
    Purpose.DomesticAppliance + Purpose.Repairs + Purpose.Education + 
    Purpose.Retraining + Purpose.Business + SavingsAccountBonds.lt.100 + 
    SavingsAccountBonds.100.to.500 + SavingsAccountBonds.500.to.1000 + 
    EmploymentDuration.gt.7 + Personal.Male.Single + OtherDebtorsGuarantors.CoApplicant + 
    Property.RealEstate + Property.Insurance + Property.CarOther + 
    Job.UnemployedUnskilled + Job.UnskilledResident + Job.SkilledEmployee, 
    data = train_data)
    
    # save all the results needed 
    coef <- rbind(t(model1$coefficients),coef)

    rsq <- rbind(summary(model1)$r.squared,rsq)

    predict(model1,newdata = test_data)
    rsqtest<- rbind(cor(test_data$Amount, predict(model1, newdata = test_data))^2,rsqtest)
}

step 4 - 9

#plot of variables
coef <- as.data.frame(coef)
hist(coef$Duration)

hist(coef$CreditHistory.NoCredit.AllPaid)

hist((coef$Personal.Male.Single))

# r squared in train
hist(rsq)

# decrease of R square from train to holdout
fall <- c((rsq - rsqtest)/rsq)
hist(fall)

#We expect the distribution to be normal and this indicate a good result
